The paper discusses an approach for specifying tasks interactively using demonstrations, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents an interface for user interaction, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (HCI), making cs.HC another likely sub-category. The approach involves training policies based on demonstrations, which is a machine learning (ML) technique, making cs.LG a possible sub-category. The Lunar Lander domain mentioned in the paper involves robotics, making cs.RO another possible sub-category. Finally, the approach involves designing agents, which falls under the category of systems and control (SY), making cs.SY a possible sub-category.
